    "body": "### Problem\n\nIf the lsp hover/floating window is closed by user, moving the cursor afterward will make nvim index `vim.w` with the invalid hover window id, hence the error.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nThe bug can be reproduced by opening a file and attaching a lsp client that supports hover method, open the hover window, closing the hover window manually, then move the cursor. The following reproduce steps use `bash-language-server` as an example.\n\n1. Install `bash-language-server`\n2. `echo \"echo 'a'\" > test.sh`\n3. `nvim --clean test.sh`\n4. `:lua vim.lsp.start({ cmd = { 'bash-language-server', 'start' } })`\n5. Put the cursor on the \"echo\" in `test.sh`\n6. Press `K` to open the lsp hover window\n7. Close the hover window by `:lua for _, win in ipairs(vim.api.nvim_list_wins()) do if vim.fn.win_gettype(win) == 'popup' then vim.api.nvim_win_close(win, {}) end end`\n8. Move the cursor and see the error message\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nShould not error if the lsp hover window is already closed\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.0-dev-1219+g46d124a933\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux 6.11.9-arch1-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty 0.14.0 (22a44757) + tmux 3.5a\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nAUR",
